{{Infobox Convention | name = Con-G | image = [[File:Con-GLogo.jpg|225px]] | caption = Con-G's logo | status = Defunct | venue = Delta Guelph Hotel and Conference Centre (2014) | location = [[Guelph]], [[Ontario]] | country = Canada | first = 2009 | last = 2014 | attendance = 1,600 in 2014<ref name="FC-2014" /> | website = http://www.con-g.com }}
'''Con-G''' was a [[non-profit]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.guelphchamber.com/find/#action=Listing&value=19481&searchID=247274&cid=119&did=21 | title = Guelph Chamber of Commerce | publisher = GuelphChamber.com | accessdate = October 23, 2012}}</ref> fan-run multigenre convention, held in February in [[Guelph]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]] from 2009<ref name="FC-2009"/> to 2014.<ref name="FC-2014"/> The convention was originally created as a Japanese [[anime convention]]<ref name="Con-G FAQ">{{cite web | url = http://www.con-g.com/information/faq/ | title = Con-G FAQ| publisher = Con-G.com | accessdate = February 9, 2011}}</ref> but subsequently covered many other aspects of [[geek culture]], such as [[Steampunk]], Sci-Fi, Fantasy, Gaming etc.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.con-g.com/information/faq/ | title = Con-G FAQ| publisher = Con-G.com | accessdate = March 14, 2012}}</ref> The name Con-G came from a combination of the words "Convention Guelph" and was a play on words on the Japanese writing system [[kanji]].<ref name="Con-G FAQ"/>
