==Events== *[[49 BC]] &ndash; [[Julius Caesar]] crosses the [[Rubicon]], signalling the start of [[Caesar's Civil War|civil war]]. *[[AD 9]] &ndash; The Western [[Han dynasty]] ends when [[Wang Mang]] claims that the divine [[Mandate of Heaven]] called for the end of the dynasty and the beginning of his own, the [[Xin dynasty]]. *[[AD 69]] &ndash; [[Lucius Calpurnius Piso Licinianus]] is appointed by [[Galba]] as [[Caesar (title)|deputy Roman Emperor]]. *[[236]] &ndash; [[Pope Fabian]] succeeds [[Pope Anterus|Anterus]] to become the twentieth pope of [[Ancient Rome|Rome]]. *[[1072]] &ndash; [[Robert Guiscard]] conquers [[Palermo]] in Sicily. *[[1430]] &ndash; [[Philip the Good]], the [[Duke of Burgundy]], establishes the [[Order of the Golden Fleece]], the most prestigious, exclusive, and expensive [[order of chivalry]] in the world.<ref name="Gibbons2013">{{cite book|last=Gibbons|first=Rachel|title=Exploring history 1400-1900: An anthology of primary sources |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=m_rHCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT65 |accessdate=2018-07-30 |date=2013-01-18 |publisher=Manchester University Press |isbn=9781847792587 |page=65 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> *[[1475]] &ndash; [[Stephen III of Moldavia]] defeats the [[Ottoman Empire]] at the [[Battle of Vaslui]]. *[[1645]] &ndash; Archbishop [[William Laud]] is beheaded for treason at the [[Tower of London]]. *[[1776]] &ndash; American Revolution : [[Thomas Paine]] publishes his pamphlet ''[[Common Sense (pamphlet)|Common Sense]]''. *[[1791]] &ndash; The [[Siege of Dunlap's Station]] begins near [[Cincinnati]] during the [[Northwest Indian War]]. *[[1806]] &ndash; Two British brigades occupy Cape Town after the [[Battle of Blaauwberg]]. *[[1812]] &ndash; The [[New Orleans (steamboat)|first steamboat]] on the [[Ohio River]] or the [[Mississippi River]] arrives in [[New Orleans]], 82 days after departing from [[Pittsburgh]]. *[[1861]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Florida]] becomes the third state to secede from the [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]]. *[[1863]] &ndash; The [[Metropolitan Railway]], the world's oldest underground railway, opens between [[Paddington tube station (Circle and Hammersmith & City lines)|Paddington]] and [[Farringdon station|Farringdon]], marking the beginning of the [[London Underground]]. *[[1870]] &ndash; [[John D. Rockefeller]] incorporates [[Standard Oil]]. *[[1901]] &ndash; The first great [[Texas]] [[Blowout (well drilling)|oil gusher]] is discovered at [[Spindletop]] in [[Beaumont, Texas]]. *[[1916]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: In the [[Erzurum Offensive]], [[Russian Empire|Russia]] defeats the Ottoman Empire. *[[1920]] &ndash; The [[Treaty of Versailles]] takes effect, officially ending World War I. * 1920 &ndash; [[League of Nations Covenant]] enters into force. On January 16 the organization holds its first council meeting, in Paris. *[[1927]] &ndash; [[Fritz Lang]]'s futuristic film ''[[Metropolis (1927 film)|Metropolis]]'' is released in Germany. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The Greek army [[Capture of Klisura Pass|captures]] [[Këlcyrë|Kleisoura]]. *[[1946]] &ndash; The first [[United Nations General Assembly|General Assembly]] of the [[United Nations]] opens in London. Fifty-one nations are represented. * 1946 &ndash; The [[Signal Corps (United States Army)|United States Army Signal Corps]] successfully conducts [[Project Diana]], bouncing [[radio wave]]s off the Moon and receiving the reflected signals. *[[1954]] &ndash; [[BOAC Flight 781]], a de Havilland DH.106 Comet 1, explodes and falls into the [[Tyrrhenian Sea]] killing 35 people. *[[1962]] &ndash; [[Apollo program]]: [[NASA]] announces plans to build the C-5 rocket [[launch vehicle]], which became known as the [[Saturn V]] Moon rocket, which launched every Apollo Moon mission. *[[1966]] &ndash; [[Tashkent Declaration]], a peace agreement between India and Pakistan signed that resolved the [[Indo-Pakistani War of 1965]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Sheikh Mujibur Rahman]] returns to the newly independent [[Bangladesh]] as president after spending over nine months in prison in [[Pakistan]]. *[[1981]] &ndash; [[Salvadoran Civil War]]: The [[Farabundo Martí National Liberation Front|FMLN]] launches its first major offensive, gaining control of most of [[Morazán Department|Morazán]] and [[Chalatenango Department|Chalatenango]] departments *[[1984]] &ndash; [[Holy See–United States relations]]: The United States and [[Holy See]] ([[Vatican City]]) re-establish full diplomatic relations after almost 117 years, overturning the [[United States Congress]]'s [[1867]] ban on public funding for such a diplomatic envoy. *[[1985]] &ndash; [[Sandinista National Liberation Front|Sandinista]] [[Daniel Ortega]] becomes president of [[Nicaragua]] and vows to continue the transformation to socialism and alliance with the Soviet Union and Cuba; American policy continues to support the [[Contras]] in their revolt against the Nicaraguan government. *[[1990]] &ndash; [[Time Warner]] is formed by the merger of [[Time Inc.]] and [[Warner Communications]]. *[[2007]] &ndash; A [[2007 Guinean general strike|general strike]] begins in [[Guinea]] in an attempt to get President [[Lansana Conté]] to resign. *[[2012]] &ndash; A [[2012 Khyber Agency bombing|bombing]] in [[Khyber Agency]], Pakistan, kills at least 30 people and 78 others injured. *[[2013]] &ndash; More than 100 people are killed and 270 injured in several [[January 2013 Pakistan bombings|bomb blasts]] in [[Pakistan]]. *[[2015]] &ndash; A [[Mozambique funeral beer poisoning|mass poisoning]] at a funeral in [[Mozambique]] involving beer that was deliberately contaminated with crocodile [[bile]] leaving at least 56 dead and nearly 200 hospitalized. * 2015 &ndash; A [[2015 Karachi traffic accident|traffic accident]] between an oil tanker truck and passenger coach en route to [[Shikarpur, Sindh|Shikarpur]] from [[Karachi]] on the [[Pakistan]] [[National Highways of Pakistan|National Highway Link Road]] near [[Gulshan-e-Hadeed]], Karachi, killing at least 62 people.
