'''''Russian Proriv!''''' ([[Cyrillic]]: Русский Прорыв, [[Russian language|Russian]] for 'Russian Breakthrough') is a Russian-language newspaper from [[Tiraspol]], the capital of [[Pridnestrovie]] (also known as [[Transnistria]]).
The paper was printed four times a month and consisted of seven folded D3-sized sheets. It had a circulation of 10,000 copies per week in 2007.
The first [[editor in chief]] was [[Roman Konoplev]] ([[Cyrillic]]: Роман Коноплев)(2007-2008).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://point.md/ro/noutati/politica/v-pridnestrovje-vishel-pervij-nomer-gazeti-russkij-proriv |script-title=ru:В Приднестровье вышел первый номер газеты «РУССКИЙ ПРОРЫВ!» |author= |date= |work= |publisher=«point.md» |accessdate=12 January 2007|language=ru}}</ref>.
